{"lemma":"مَثَلُ","slug":"مَثَلُ","root":"م.ث.ل","root_slug":"م-ث-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ث-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَثَل","root":"مثل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":88},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":27},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43499","n43500","n43506","n43507","n4603"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to resemble, to look like"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to imitate, to copy"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to compare, to liken"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to represent, to mean, to signify, to stand for"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to present oneself, to stand, to appear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to come forth, to come forward, to enter, to appear"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to portray, to play, to present"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to represent, to stand for, to be exemplary for, to account for","examples":[{"text":"يهاجر هو وأتباعه من مكة إلى المدينة المنورة (المعروفة آنذاك باسم يثرب) في وقت لاحق من عام 622 ويُمَثِّلُ هذا الحدث٬ الهجرة٬ بداية التقويم الإسلامي.","english":"He and his followers migrated from Mecca to Medina (then known as Yathrib) later in 622 AD. This event, the Hijra, marks the beginning of the Islamic calendar."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make to resemble, to make to look like"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make similar, to make analogous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to assimilate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to quote as example"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to compare, to liken"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to punish severely, to treat harshly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to maim, to mutilate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something similar","examples":[{"text":"رَجُلٌ مِثْلُهُ","english":"a man like him"},{"text":"فِي مِثْلِ هٰذِهِ ٱلظُّرُوفِ","english":"under circumstances like these"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"resemblance, similarity, likeness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"image"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"equivalent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"likeness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"metaphor, simile, parable"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"proverb, adage"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"example"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lesson"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ideal, model"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of مِثَال (miṯāl)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of مِثَال (miṯāl)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew מָשָׁל (mašál, “example”).\n\nCognate with Hebrew מָשָׁל (mashál, “proverb, allegory”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43499","headword_ar":"مَثَلَ","root":"mvl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvuwlN","text_ar":"مُثُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K, &c.;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavula","text_ar":"مَثُلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stood erect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K, &c.;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona yadayohi","text_ar":"بَيْنَ يَدَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, &c.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavala bihi","text_ar":"مَثَلَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvolapN","text_ar":"مُثْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He mutilated him; castrated him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a sheep or goat. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"djn","text_ar":"دجن"},{"kind":"text","text":", from a trad.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43500","headword_ar":"مَثَّلَ","root":"mvl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see a verse of Kutheiyir in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwd","text_ar":"رود"},{"kind":"text","text":", conj. 4. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mav~alahu","text_ar":"مَثَّلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ab~ahahu","text_ar":"شَبَّهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43506","headword_ar":"مِثْلٌ","root":"mvl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A like; a similar person"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing; match; fellow; an analogue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, &c.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nid~N","text_ar":"نِدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalN","text_ar":"بَدَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A likeness, resemblance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"semblance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An equivalent; a requital."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivola","text_ar":"مِثْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", used as a denotative of state, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Like."},{"kind":"text","text":"Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mar~a mivola Albaroqi","text_ar":"مَرَّ مِثْلَ البَرْقِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed like the lightning."},{"kind":"text","text":"See an ex. in the Kur li. 23; and another, from Sakhr-el-Gheí, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroDN","text_ar":"فَرْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43507","headword_ar":"مَثَلٌ","root":"mvl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SifapN","text_ar":"صِفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A description, condition, state, case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (S, K, &c.;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSofN","text_ar":"وَصْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the same]: (Msb:) or this is a mistake: (Mbr, AAF, TA:) or it may be a tropical signification: (MF, TA:) for in the language of the Arabs it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a description by way of comparison:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AAF, TA:) you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mvl zyd mvl","text_ar":"مثل زيد مثل"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flAn","text_ar":"فلان"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The description of Zeyd, by way of comparison,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the condition, &c., is that of such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmivAalu","text_ar":"المِثاَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHa*owu","text_ar":"الحَذْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mbr, TA:) it is metaphorically applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a condition, state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is important, strange, or wonderful. (Ksh, Bd in ii. 16.) The phrase here given is more literally, and better, rendered,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The similitude of Zeyd is the similitude,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is that, of such a one;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for a similitude is a description by way of comparison. ―         -b2-  You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu mavalFA","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ مَثَلًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lika*aA","text_ar":"لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an expression or the like)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be descriptive, by way of comparison, of such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA passim.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavalN lika*aA","text_ar":"مَثَلٌ لِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An expression denoting, by way of similitude, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Almavali","text_ar":"عَلَى المَثَلِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As indicative of resemblance"},{"kind":"text","text":"to something. ―         -b4-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalN","text_ar":"بَدَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","Mbr","AAF","TA","MF"]},{"entry_id":"n4603","headword_ar":"مُثِلٌّ","root":"vl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man (S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abounding in what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"val~ap","text_ar":"ثَلَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, K. [See 4,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aval~u","text_ar":"اَثَلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Golius with this word, as syn. therewith, and as from the S and K, is not in either of those Lexicons.])"}],"source_refs":["S","M"]}]}}